Additionally, it is mentioned that academics and policymakers alike draw on her insights to address contemporary political challenges.

Furthermore, the documents also discuss the relationship between Hannah Arendt and Carl Schmitt, noting that they share some similarities in their thought, such as a critique of liberal proceduralism and a focus on the importance of public affairs. The documents also mention that Samuel Moyn has shown that Arendt's account of modern politics can be fruitfully read as a critical engagement with Schmitt, in parts replicating his theological reading of sovereignty while insisting on a secular alternative.
